<div id="banner">
	<h1>Media Concentration</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>Lessig notes that the FCC’s rulemaking on media concentration is quickly approaching.</p>

<p>Educate yourself: Lessig’s blog (<a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/lessig/blog/archives/cat_free_culture.shtml">free culture</a>, <a href="http://cyberlaw.stanford.edu/lessig/blog/archives/cat_bad_law.shtml">bad law</a> — search for “MediaCon”), <a href="http://archive.salon.com/ent/clear_channel/">Salon’s Clear Channel archive</a></p>

<p>Take action: <a href="http://www.moveon.org/stopthefcc/">send a note to your congressmen and the FCC</a>.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, <a href="http://www.salon.com/comics/tomo/2003/05/12/tomo/story.jpg">Tom Tomorrow reminds us how important the uncompromising liberal media is</a>.</p>

